features = ['age', "fnlwgt", "education_num", "capital_gain", "capital_loss", "hours_per_week"]
i = 1

plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))

for feature in features:
    plt.subplot(2, 3, i)
    train[feature].hist(bins=20)   #plt.hist(train[feature], bins=20)  .
    plt.title(feature)
    i += 1

박스플롯 (boxplot)¶

boxplot

  • (outlier)( ) : .
  • (maximum) : Q3+1.5*IQR (IQR=Q3-Q1. )
  • 3 (Q3)(upper quartile) : 75% .
  • 2 (Q2)(median) : 50% . .
  • 1 (Q1)(lower quartile) : 25% .
  • (minimun) : Q1-1.5*IQR
